remains an obscure subject, as we do not possess an extensive and detailed presentation of its whole narrative design. Vasileios Liotsakis tries to satisfy this central desideratum of the Thucydidean scholarship by offering a thorough description of the compositional plan, which, in his opinion, Thucydides put into effect in the last 109 chapters of his work. His study elaborates on the structural parts of the book, their details, and the various techniques through which Thucydides composed his narration in order to reach the internal cohesion of these chapters as well as their close connection to the rest of the History. Liotsakis offers us an original approach not only of Book 8 but also of the whole work, since his observations reshape our overall view of the History.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aHistoriographie. 4aPeloponnesischer Krieg. 4aThukydides. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aHistoriography.  aPeloponnesian War.  aThucydides.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2017z9783110547733oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831105320980 cprintz978311053207440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311053307140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110533071423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110533071/original  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 20